## Project Installation

### Backend (server)

1.  Clone the repository: `git clone https://github.com/priyankayadav33/job-portal.git`
2.  Navigate to the `server` directory: `cd server`
3.  Install dependencies: `npm install` or `yarn install`
4.  Create a `.env` file in the `server` directory (see [Environment Variables](#environment-variables)).
5.  Start the server: `npm start` or `yarn start`

### Frontend (client)

1.  Navigate to the `client` directory: `cd client`
2.  Install dependencies: `npm install` or `yarn install`
3.  Create a `.env` file in the `client` directory (see [Environment Variables](#environment-variables)).
4.  Start the development server: `npm start` or `yarn start`

## Deployment

### Backend Deployment

1.  Choose a hosting provider (e.g., Heroku, AWS, Google Cloud, Netlify).
2.  Configure your server for the chosen platform.
3.  Deploy your backend code.

### Frontend Deployment

1.  Build a production-ready version of your React app: `npm run build` or `yarn build`
2.  Deploy the contents of the `build` directory to a static hosting provider (e.g., Netlify, Vercel, AWS S3) or a web server.

